The society for professional Background Screeners has appointed trustees as it prepares to commence activities as an independent non-profit trade association of professional background screeners in Nigeria. Officers have also been elected to run the affairs of the association that aims to promote ethical business practices, foster awareness of the need for background check as a security risk imperative, and establish acceptable and evidenced-based standards for background screening professionals in Nigeria. SPBS also aims to advance industry objectives by providing the standards, competencies development, operating framework, support, and forum for practice-exchange of innovation and ideas, with the use of technology. According to a statement, the body will also promote best practices for professional background screeners in Nigeria while collaborating with enterprise and the government on the activities of background screeners. It will also educate and sensitise the public on background screening and related services The statement quoted the Chairman, SPBS, Mr. Kola Olugbodi, as saying that the Chief Executive Officer of Risk Control Services, Mr. Femi Ajayi, was appointed as the Chairman of the Board of Trustees, while the Managing Director of Proton Security Services, Col. Ademola Onalaja (retd.) would serve as Secretary of the board. Members of the Board of Trustees are Mr. Wale Olaoye [Chief Executive Officer, Halogen Group); Mr. Kola Olugbodi (Chief Executive Officer, Background Check International), and Mr. Bolaji Olamiju (Chief Executive Officer, Trapezoid Limited). Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com